ternity—reconfigured as birth is transformed?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChildbirthxIndia, South. 0aChildbirthzIndia, South. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  abiomedical.  abirth rate.  abirth stories.  achildbirth.  aclass system.  aclassism.  acolonialism.  acontemporary.  aethnographers.  aethnography.  afeminism.  afeminist.  agender studies.  agender.  aglobal.  aglobalization.  ahome birth.  ahospital birth.  aindia.  ainternational.  alower class.  amaternity.  amedical technology.  amidwifery.  amidwives.  amodern world.  anational.  aparenting.  apostcolonial.  apregnancy.  asouth india.  atamil nadu.  atechnology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093539640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935396423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520935396/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles